en: The cup was found at Vulci in 1828/1829 or 1831 on the estate of Lucien Bonaparte, Prince of Canino and younger brother of Napoleon. It was presented to the American Philosophical Society on June 17, 1836 by Joseph Bonaparte, ex-king of Spain and a member of the American Philosophical Society from 1823 to 1844. It has been on extended loan to the University Museum, Philadelphia, since 1968.
There is some discoloration and pitting of the surface.
Type B kylix. The bowl is very large and flat. The alien foot is signed by Nikosthenes.
